data.title: Lake Ontario: Rochester, New York FM Bandscan
data.meta_description: A list of FM radio stations as commonly received in the Rochester / Webster, New York area, part of a series of Great Lakes bandscans by Chris Kadlec.
data.meta_site_name: :: the online home of chris kadlec ::
data.text:
Go back to the Lake Ontario bandscan series | Return to the coastal bandscans index

Webster Park is just 10 miles (a 25-minute drive) outside downtown Rochester, New York’s third largest city. The park is a fantastic location that combines both low and high listening options, is somewhat roughly in the center of Lake Ontario’s southern shore, and is close to only one major metro area: itself. Because of its location, everything from Buffalo and Toronto east to Kingston, Montréal, Ottawa, and Syracuse can be heard here. However, Rochester has nearly 40 local stations to sift through, a great number of them being translators.

Recommendations for this radio site: Webster Park in itself isn’t a very happening place. For those who want to stay close to Rochester but avoid the high cost of a hotel for the night, Webster Park Campground is a good choice. Do note, however, that the park and the area surrounding the park are very dark at night. In the daytime, there are numerous trails to explore in the park and though close to Rochester, it’s in a rather quiet semi-rural residential area. As with any larger city, there are plenty of things to do in Rochester in the summer.

Seabreeze Amusement Park is nearby. However, it should be mentioned that the Irondequoit Bay Outlet Bridge, a swing truss bridge just west of the park that connects Webster to suburban Irondequoit beside the lakeshore, is open only in winter, so otherwise short trips become unnecessarily lengthy. There are other beach sites to the west, though with less privacy and the likelihood to encounter more people. Four miles to the west along the same road is Sandbar Park, while on the opposite side of Rochester is Ontario Beach Park, another county park, albeit more developed. The city of Rochester itself has plenty of parkland to wander and near limitless things to do if you have a day to spare.
